test_case_results.title: Page should consist of HTML heading element with text content as "Reviews"
Page should consist of HTML button element with testid attribute value as "leftArrow"
Page should consist of HTML button element with testid attribute value as "rightArrow"
Page should consist of HTML image element with alt as "left arrow" and src attribute value as URL for left arrow image
Page should consist of HTML image element with alt as "right arrow" and src attribute value as URL for right arrow image
Page should initially display the first review, and consist of HTML image element with alt value equal to the "username" value in reviewsList provided
Page should initially display the first review, and consist of HTML image element with alt value equal to the "username" and src attribute value equal to the "imgUrl" value in reviewsList provided
Page should initially display the first review, and consist of HTML paragraph element with text content equal to the "username" value in reviewsList provided
Page should initially display the first review, and consist of HTML paragraph element with text content equal to the "companyName" value in reviewsList provided
Page should initially display the first review, and consist of HTML paragraph element with text content equal to the "description" value in reviewsList provided

When the right arrow is clicked, the page should consist of an HTML image element with alt value equal to the "username" and src attribute value equal to the "imgUrl" value of the next review in reviewsList provided
When the right arrow is clicked, the page should consist of HTML paragraph elements with "username", "companyName", and "description" of the next review in reviewsList provided
When the left arrow is clicked, the page should consist of an HTML image element with alt attribute value equal to the "imgUrl" value of the previous review in reviewsList provided
When the left arrow is clicked, the page should consist of HTML paragraph elements with "username", "companyName", and "description" of the previous review in reviewsList provided
When viewing the first review, there should not be any state change when the HTML button element with testid attribute value as "leftArrow" is clicked
When viewing the last review, there should not be any state change when the HTML button element with testid attribute value as "rightArrow" is clicked
